<p><i><b>On Intelligence: How a New Understanding of the Brain will Lead to the Creation of Truly Intelligent Machines</b></i> is a book by <a href="/wiki/Palm_(PDA)" title="Palm (PDA)">Palm Pilot</a>-inventor <a href="/wiki/Jeff_Hawkins" title="Jeff Hawkins">Jeff Hawkins</a> with <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a></i> science writer <a href="/w/index.php?title=Sandra_Blakeslee&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sandra Blakeslee (page does not exist)">Sandra Blakeslee</a>. The book explains Hawkins' <a href="/wiki/Memory-prediction_framework" title="Memory-prediction framework">memory-prediction framework</a> theory of the <a href="/wiki/Brain" title="Brain">brain</a> and describes some of its consequences. (Times Books: 2004, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0805074562" class="internal">ISBN 0-8050-7456-2</a>)</p>
